<tableCitation id="C5BE7AC1664E77C64F3C2BCB7D99F687" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. List of Xanthopygus species sensu Herman and their current name based on this paper. Bold type font on the first column indicates taxa included in the phylogenetic analysis. Taxa not included in this analysis but transferred to Photinopygus have all the diagnostic features of Photinopygus. Similarly, taxa that remained in Xanthopygus but were not included in the analysis have all the diagnostic features of Xanthopygus sensu novo." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/817BF073FC00ACBD32CE01DDA19F045E" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" tableUuid="817BF073FC00ACBD32CE01DDA19F045E">1</tableCitation>
for complete names).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4D236B983324179802E7C023BD478DEC" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="BEEF3AE197E6FDE9C09804EC2A635721" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A52B90099B90224A7B77747F29D7A9C9" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
This genus can be distinguished from all other genera in 
<taxonomicName id="C707E7755D6D80A083E87D3BE33E42AA" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Staphylinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Xanthopygina">Xanthopygina</taxonomicName>
based on the combination of the following characteristics: head shape rectangular; posterior margin of head slightly extended posteriad on each side of the neck (apomorphy; except in 
<taxonomicName id="393C750CBF6C6FB0E51879BDD5C86165" genus="Ph." lsidName="Ph. corcovadoensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="corcovadoensis">
<emphasis id="528E421932EA9F25E9BE2C399BCF5B33" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Ph. corcovadoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1F2CAF33BB6AB57C63F6903993C91917" genus="Ph." lsidName="Ph. mirabilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="05129002FF676331C2BE1698E213421A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Ph. mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); antennomeres 1-5 elongate; labial palpomere 3 not securiform; medium size eyes; superior marginal line of pronotal hypomeron not continuing to anterior margin; postcoxal process present; pronotum with sparse micropunctures but no transverse lines visible at 70
<normalizedToken id="D9DF3A4CA676D932E38D588FC4D653F6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
magnification (apomorphy); mesoscutellum without dense micropunctures (apomorphy); mesoventral process narrow and rounded (apomorphy); metatarsi with setose dorsal surface (apomorphy); tergite 3 (at minimum, some species 3-4 or 3-5) with arch-like carina; and sternite 7 in males with emargination at posterior margin. For a list of characters that distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="4F68CABB0050396A182F6D6733A77EF6" authority="Chatzimanolis, 2021" authorityName="Chatzimanolis" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Photinopygus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Photinopygus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DDF52B7A865C81A5FA6CA9BEA52650F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Photinopygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="0385D0159E07FAE04F940B692D18BC35" authorityName="Kraatz" authorityYear="1857" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xanthopygus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xanthopygus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2B88C07BDC21423ED535FC8BF32EEBAE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Xanthopygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see Table 
<tableCitation id="C493C8EF19BC6984C7DA7F73AD861E56" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="T2" captionText="Table 2. List of taxonomic characters that distinguish species of Xanthopygus from Photinopygus. Numbers next to characters refers to the numbers in the data matrix. For a full list of characters and character states see Material and Methods, and for the mapping of the characters on the phylogenetic tree see Suppl. material 3." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/4C02FE6978BC23F3C1313AC3D5A82848" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" tableUuid="4C02FE6978BC23F3C1313AC3D5A82848">2</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2765BE4FBCA2D4EB722649CC84A3C2AC" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3DC12C8F9C61EAE01CD67338904C7EA1" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="86DEF671022AF4BC8F4153FFAB622E6B" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
The name is a combination of the Greek words 
<normalizedToken id="6C61A14AC7E8AA47FD8137430EF6FC01" originalValue="φωτεινός">φωτεινός</normalizedToken>
(shining, bright) and 
<normalizedToken id="1F4EDCC227554150457B361DF9471FA7" originalValue="πυγή">πυγή</normalizedToken>
(rump), and refers to the bright coloration of abdominal segments 7 and 8. The name is masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2724C33CF65FD012CC1243626BDBB3D0" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="5B06C2985D1A5115CE0AAA3037ACE0A8" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E082A70B03455A3D860B52C32A238F68" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
A formal revision of the genus is forthcoming (Chatzimanolis in preparation) where all species belonging to this genus will be treated and illustrated. Even though some of the species transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="14E97D1C9EF7E7E97B1D211399FCC550" authority="Chatzimanolis, 2021" authorityName="Chatzimanolis" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Photinopygus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Photinopygus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3F216BF5D9163AAE4098BEDAC1A5E7DF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Photinopygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were not included in the phylogenetic analysis, they can be confidently placed in this genus since they have all the diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName id="3F465CB71E00E0325408C1BD95F3A4D2" authority="Chatzimanolis, 2021" authorityName="Chatzimanolis" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Photinopygus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Photinopygus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AFE8C9BC7F1C6B4BF049D5CA650F37A7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Photinopygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Tables 
<tableCitation id="554927995E085BA6FC7CDDFE6BF01A40" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. List of Xanthopygus species sensu Herman and their current name based on this paper. Bold type font on the first column indicates taxa included in the phylogenetic analysis. Taxa not included in this analysis but transferred to Photinopygus have all the diagnostic features of Photinopygus. Similarly, taxa that remained in Xanthopygus but were not included in the analysis have all the diagnostic features of Xanthopygus sensu novo." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/817BF073FC00ACBD32CE01DDA19F045E" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" tableUuid="817BF073FC00ACBD32CE01DDA19F045E">1</tableCitation>
and 
<tableCitation id="CD490FFB82AF2AF9923BEC8604B7AD8C" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="T2" captionText="Table 2. List of taxonomic characters that distinguish species of Xanthopygus from Photinopygus. Numbers next to characters refers to the numbers in the data matrix. For a full list of characters and character states see Material and Methods, and for the mapping of the characters on the phylogenetic tree see Suppl. material 3." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/4C02FE6978BC23F3C1313AC3D5A82848" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" tableUuid="4C02FE6978BC23F3C1313AC3D5A82848">2</tableCitation>
for details).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
